## Step 1: Add new type variants and xs size

Update the Variant type to include booking, poll, caldav:

```typescript
type Variant = 'pending' | 'confirmed' | 'active' | 'cancelled' | 'draft' | 'booking' | 'poll' | 'caldav';
type Size = 'xs' | 'sm' | 'md';
```

## Step 2: Add optional label prop

Add a label prop that overrides the default mapping:

```typescript
interface Props {
    variant?: Variant;
    size?: Size;
    label?: string;
}

let { variant = 'pending', size = 'md', label }: Props = $props();
```

## Step 3: Update labels mapping

```typescript
const labels: Record<Variant, string> = {
    pending: 'Pending',
    confirmed: 'Confirmed',
    active: 'Active',
    cancelled: 'Cancelled',
    draft: 'Draft',
    booking: 'Booking',
    poll: 'Poll',
    caldav: 'CalDAV'
};
```

## Step 4: Use label prop or fallback to mapping

```svelte
<span class="badge badge-{variant} badge-{size}">
    {label ?? labels[variant]}
</span>
```

## Step 5: Add CSS for new variants and xs size

```css
/* New size */
.badge-xs {
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem;
}

/* New variants */
.badge-booking {
    background: var(--emerald, #10b981);
}

.badge-poll {
    background: var(--violet, #8b5cf6);
}

.badge-caldav {
    background: var(--emerald, #10b981);
}
```

## Step 6: Run type check

```bash
cd frontend && pnpm check
```

## Step 7: Commit

```bash
git add frontend/src/lib/components/ui/Badge.svelte
git commit -m "feat(Badge): add type variants (booking, poll, caldav), xs size, and label prop"
```

